<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-22198] camel-resilience4j - throwExceptionWhenHalfOpenOrOpenState is not always thrown if in OPEN / HALF_OPEN state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-22198</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18507&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-18507&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
when the state is OPEN / HALF_OPEN then the exception&#160;is not thrown.&lt;br/&gt;
That is a bit weird as its resilience4j that throws NotPermittedException which we then detect in Camel and then just rethrow and that was the how its implemented. So the description could say that its only when this happens. But I think we should try to see if we can also make it happen when the state is OPEN / HALF_OPEN. We can see the&#160;state in JMX (or with camel-jbang CLI).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
