                            <comment id="17986128" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 25 Jun 2025 12:11:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh so this is only relevant if you do not have a fallback - as the fallback is there to be executed if its not success. And as such the exception should not be thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its only being thrown when you do NOT have fallback and that it was rejected by resilience4j (open) or when in half-open when it was not attempted but rejected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this is more of a documentation issue about this option in Camel to describe this better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
